9) Balance Guardrails (unchanged, restated for reference)

TTK targets: 8–14 s for equal-tier duels within a class.

Energy sustain: baseline builds sustain ≥8–10 s of continuous fire + maneuver; Advanced +15–25%.

Mobility ladder: Strike > Escort > Line > Capital (turn rates & accel).

Sensor ladder: DRADIS increases with size; Visual only slightly.

FTL ladder: larger hulls tend to more range and higher cost; Command frames may discount transponder costs.

Slot identity: Enforce role slot advantages rigorously.

10) Feature Notes Specific to Named Frames (context for coders)

Viper Mk VII (Strike/Multi-Role): balanced strike with reliable PD/missile denial when fitted; excels in angles; survivability via Avoidance + modest Armor.

(Examples retained for future entries:) Glaive (Escort/Command), Vanir (Line/Command), Brimir (Capital/Carrier)—add their concrete stat sheets under Stats Library as you provide them.

11) QA & Acceptance Checklist (per ship)

Spec sheet complete and unit-correct (no missing fields; no invented numbers).

Slots obey §4 role rules; Advanced variant shows correct deltas.

Arcs/gimbals defined per mount; any frame trait documented.

Economy (purchase/upgrade/operating) present and coherent.

Pre-installs spawn correctly.

Movement & energy behavior matches numbers (e.g., measured Boost Speed ≤ configured value).

Sensors/lock feel consistent with DRADIS/Visual numbers.

FTL respects range/charge/cost; cooldown enforced.
